This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object recognition and visual exemplars. It also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests it could also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to extract semantic representations, which could place it in the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the use of benchmark datasets for evaluation suggests it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
